# TASK_PACKET

Task ID
CRUSHR-FORMAT-10

Title
Metadata pruning experiment to identify the minimal necessary archive truth surfaces

Role
BUILDER

Objective
Use the results of FORMAT-08 and FORMAT-09 to aggressively simplify the experimental archive design and determine which metadata layers, if any, are actually necessary for recovery.

Current evidence shows:

- metadata placement strategy produced no measurable recovery difference
- metadata survival counts remained zero across the Phase-09 audit
- recovery behavior is being driven primarily by self-identifying payload blocks plus salvage reasoning
- current metadata layers appear to add archive size and complexity without measurable resilience gain

This packet is an evidence-driven pruning experiment.

The goal is not to add new metadata.
The goal is to remove or demote metadata layers and measure whether recovery behavior changes.

This remains experimental and opt-in.

